-- Pertamina Buys Nigerian, Algerian Crude Oil for December Delivery From BP
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   S c h m o l l i n g e r
-- 2010-10-20T06:47:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/pertamina-buys-nigerian-algerian-crude-oil-for-december-delivery-from-bp.html
PT Pertamina , Indonesia’s state oil
company, purchased a cargo of Nigeria’s Qua Iboe crude and one
of Algeria’s Saharan Blend from BP Plc for delivery in December,
said two traders who participate in the market. The company
earlier this month bought about 2 million barrels of Bonny Light
oil.  Details of the purchase are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
